    {
      "start_time": 418,
      "end_time": 480,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "\"Negra Triste\". Performed by Ruth Fernandez. ",
              "bold": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Sad Black Woman"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Sad Black woman because the Black man has died because the Black man has slept never again to enjoy the celebration— only the Black woman remains."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "She does not stop crying oh her sorrow. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "She is sad, alone she weeps her grief she weeps her sorrow and her pain."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The Black man she loved so deeply is now in the realms of God."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "She is heartbroken mourning her love, mourning her Black man, the one she loved so much."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
