        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Welmo raps again. The sensation of taste, the touch of the fabric, and the sweat mingle together. Heartbeats quicken, a feverish temperature that healed him. Don't be silent, for if I am silent, I am not free. Calling and responding, resistance and audacity, even with the chains 24 hours a day. My voice travels actively, knowing that perhaps I will never see the light of day again. Drum, give me the essence of the sound of your soul. Drum, watch over my sleep with your sweet melody."
